The Heathen beholding theſe glorious Works of the Creation, had thereby a fear of a Deity impreſt upon their hearts, which was the occaſion of that Atheiſtical Speech of the Poet;
Primus in Orbe Deos fecit timor.
Fear • irſt made gods upon the Earth.

For what-ever is the firſt Original of any Good, hath the whole of that Good in it ſelf; as the Sun that is the Original of Light, hath all Light in it ſelf; and ſo the Sea, with reſpect to Water. Now God is the Original of all that Good that is in the Creature, of what-ever kind it is, and therefore the whole of all Good is in himſelf. Here we have Unity bringing forth Plurality, and all Plurality eminently comprehended in Unity. As Du Bartas divinely to this purpoſe ſpeaks;
Ere Time,Du Bart. firſt week, p. 5. Form, Subſtance, Place, to be themſelves attain'd;
All God in all things was, and All in God remain'd.
